SIMPLE: harmonious
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Harmonious
<hw>Har*mo"ni*ous</hw> <pr>(h⟦aum⟧r*m⟦omac⟧"n⟦icr⟧*⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>harmonieux</ets>. See
<er>Harmony</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Adapted to each other; having
parts proportioned to each other; symmetrical.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>God hath made the intellectual world <qex>harmonious</qex> and
beautiful without us.</q> <rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Acting together to a common end; agreeing in action
or feeling; living in peace and friendship; <as>as, an
<ex>harmonious</ex> family</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Vocally or musically concordant; agreeably
consonant; symphonious.</def></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Har*mo"ni*ous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Har*mo"ni*ous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Harmoniphon</ent>⟦br⟧
